        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 4:09PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 409 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Rising Fawn, or 7 miles
south of Trenton, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Ringgold, Trenton, Fort Oglethorpe, Rossville, Chickamauga, Lookout
Mountain, Chattanooga Valley, Blue Spring, Fairview, Chattanooga
Valley, Cloudland Canyon State Park, Cooper Heights, Rock Spring,
Rising Fawn, Noble, Lakeview, Indian Springs, Wood Station,
Graysville, and Wildwood.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
